Introduced
Second Regular Session 124th General Assembly (2026)
SENATE RESOLUTION ____
MR. PRESIDENT:
I offer the following resolution and move its adoption:
1 A SENATE RESOLUTION honoring Nora Callaway.
2 Whereas, Nora Callaway, a third-grade student at Crisman
3 Elementary School in Portage Township has been named the
4 recipient of the Distinguished Student Award from the Indiana
5 Association for the Gifted (IAG);
6 Whereas, The IAG award program is designed to celebrate
7 student excellence while also highlighting the unique
8 educational needs of gifted learners throughout Indiana;
9 Whereas, Each year, only one student from across the state
10 of Indiana is chosen to receive this award, making Nora’s
11 selection an extraordinary accomplishment;
12 Whereas, Nora’s achievement reflects not only her
13 dedication and talents, but also the commitment of educators
14 who foster student growth and encourage excellence;
15 Whereas, Nora was nominated by her second-grade
16 teacher, Lil Falk, in recognition of her outstanding academic
17 abilities, creativity, and leadership qualities and her selection
18 marks a historic milestone, as she is the first student from
2026 DR 3844/DI ol

2
1 Portage Township Schools to receive the Distinguished Student
2 Award; and
3 Whereas, This achievement serves as an inspiration to
4 students across the Portage Township Schools community and
5 Indiana: Therefore,
6 Be it resolved by the Senate of the
7 General Assembly of the State of Indiana:
8 SECTION 1. That the Indiana Senate honors Nora
9 Callaway for her outstanding accomplishment.
10 SECTION 2. The Secretary of the Senate is hereby directed
11 to transmit a copy of this Resolution to Nora Callaway, Portage
12 Township Schools, Crisman Elementary School, and Lil Falk.
